medic suppli ar run out i did not studi nurs i wa a student of biomed engin but i had to cut my studi short becaus of the war it wa my dream to studi medicin and iron that dream came true while my other dream vanish becaus of the war it s realli hard to be a nurs in eastern aleppo it just got much harder becaus all of the hospit and medic point have been bomb out of servic we ve had to move our oper and patient to home we prepar the home the best wai we can so that we can receiv as mani patient as possibl but there ar never enough medic suppli especi steril tool and painkil we can t offer our patient the most basic medic care we can t even give our patient clean blanket thei ar forc to us blanket fill with the blood of other patient thei don t have a choic the clean ladi can t find the time to wash or dry the blood stain blanket patient die smell their own blood thei die becaus of the lack of sterilis and cold we ar constantli receiv huge influx of civilian injur due to the shell and bomb which put us under extrem and constant pressur to address all of their need at onc mani error have been made becaus we ar overload with patient and have a shortag of medic staff there ar situat where we have patient die while wait on a major surgeri becaus our doctor ar so busi attend to dozen of other patient who ar also in desper need of medic care we lose patient that could ve been save if we had second to spare on of the critic care nurs name keffah wa kill the dai befor yesterdai with the death of everi doctor or nurs we die more and more and there is no time to rest or eat not even for a minut doctor and nurs eat while work even if we did find the time to sleep we can t stop think of the peopl that ar dy while we ar rest the pictur or quot that you see in the media can t even begin to convei the intens fatigu and feel of helpless we ar face in thi citi thi tragic situat ha stop me from have a life i m not marri i have no time to studi or for person activ i no longer have the time to even check on my mother the onli time that i can see her is when i m suppos to be sleep i haven t sat down on sinc yesterdai at 6am till 6pm thi even but i will continu my work so that everyon know we did our best to save peopl from thi tragic situat we ar in even if thei destroi everi singl hospit in eastern aleppo i will never give up we will continu work to help the injur and sick if our hospit get bomb we will move to the next hospit and continu our work even if it ultim cost me my life i have noth left to lose

us and made martyr of us onli we would carri our martyr on our shoulder with pride all of us now stand in the veri front row i look back now and rememb a mother who said to me it is our duti to sacrific my son i believ her word were genuin for the blood on her hand and her son laid still on her lap were pure wit to thi i look back now and rememb the solidar of human from around the world who stood by us and offer what thei could and said we love you and support you we ar forev in debt to them i look back now and rememb my friend the onli peopl i trust all di becaus thei believ becaus thei were beauti human be far braver than i i look back now and rememb my father as he stood on syrian soil for the veri first time in year and scream into the crowd in binnish we poet write with pen but you the peopl you have written poetri with your blood i look back now and rememb bara al bouhsi strip hi rank of hi shoulder and throw hi weapon to the ground swear that he would never kill to gain justic onli to die with hi camera in hi hand i look back now and rememb the brother of a tortur revolutionari he could not cope to imagin what hi brother wa go through hi brother di as did he on a mission to reliev him of hi pain i look back now and rememb syrian of all color open their door to freedom onli to welcom murder in who would attempt destroi their live i look back now and rememb flee syria and look back at my countri across the border with shame i took pictur that dai to remind me of that feel that shame i look back and now and rememb the look of my brother face as he watch the pain of our peopl wreck their insan hi word sink in me hi heart break my veri essenc    i look back now and rememb who i wa befor all thi sure that that still not what i want now i could never give in to that i love the peopl i met in thi revolut i look back now and remind myself that even if there is no road forward there is no turn back even if we must build our path each individu and meet each other somewher sooner or later there is no turn back from now on if i am ask to rest i will sai i look back now and rememb there is no reason to rest for there is no reason to forget rami jarrah

heart to do my job becaus when you enter an area that s be bomb you take the risk of never come back aliv but peopl need my help and i want to do anyth i can to help them the feel i get from save live bomb recent we haven t been abl to get fuel for our ambul almost all of the injur ar be taken to medic point by bicycl or wagon that ar normal us for sell veget it s a scene that cannot be describ man interrupt him let him in he s a doctor i wish i had not been in that hospit yesterdai and that i did not see what i saw a sea of blood and the wound doctor and medic were swim in it i move through row of injur peopl all ly on the ground in a critic condit and each tri to muster some strength to motion to me with their hand or to whimper anyth that express their pain thei want to send me the voic came down to us as if from abov we all listen attent to thi voic hope it will sai someth to calm us down the voic start gui empti the intens care unit the warplan ha launch a second strike and a third and and a tenth and i begin to see the injuri multipli the number of death multipli and i realiz there is no more blood for transfus no more sanit medic equip and no more serum bag but we continu work as if it s the end of the world even the wound look at you with the ey of those who have been condemn to hope and as soon as you re done with an injur civilian anoth look at you with arriv right after the first strike and in that moment i wish i could be shatter into hundr of piec so that each piec could treat someon s brother or mother or father then my colleagu anoth doctor help treat the wound yell come check out my cousin i think he di but i can t make a final decis anoth on yell doctor come see thi gui that i tri to reviv i think he s dead other peopl stand around and ask that gui breath from hi neck is there anyth we can do to help him doctor is there anyth i can help you with i turn around and see an ophthalmologist who came from ghouta to share my burden and carri out the duti that god ha thrust upon him same with the pediatrician and same with the neurologist becaus thei see all the wound as famili syrian ar on peopl a few hour have elaps sinc the air raid and i now look across the intens care unit at least the ground ha been empti of it injur although the bed ar still all occupi i begin to feel that the situat is a bit more manag now thi is when the rescu oper end and the real catastroph begin the syria civil defens team have document more than death soul that have left thi life famili who have lost a member women who have lost a son a husband or a brother men who have lost a son a daughter a husband a father or a sibl i move through the oper room and see exhaust doctor who have perform more than surgeri dure the past few hour thei have seen gut continu and follow him the white helmet carri the boi to the ambul and laid him on the chair i kept film it is then that i realiz how traumat the boi wa and i chang the camera from film to take a still pictur the tear start to drop as i took the photo it is not the first time i ve cri i have cri mani time while film traumat children i alwai cry we war photograph alwai cry last night everyon cri omran s affect me becaus he wa silent he didn t cry he didn t sai a word he wa shock i thought of my dai old babi girl i thought to myself it could be her it could be ani child in aleppo or syria moham hardan a video editor with the aleppo media center write to you about life in besieg aleppo pleas read it and share i move to the regim control part of aleppo in june when i start studi aviat engin at univers i us thi student life as a cover for six month whilst i report on regim crime it wa a riski decis i could have been arrest or expos thankfulli i have a strong heart aleppo is our citi and i believ it s our duti to protect it by document these crime i left aleppo for a while on a scholarship to turkei but i return when the first sieg start in i couldn t stai in turkei ani longer my mind wa in my citi and my countri in life befor the sieg i us to wake up drink coffe eat biscuit and drive to work i didn t experi the psycholog stress i do todai we us to find everyth we want in the market due to the current sieg there is noth left in the market nowadai we onli eat thyme and drink tea if it s avail the onli wai to get from on place to anoth is by walk becaus there is no fuel left photograph ar no longer abl to cover everyth that is happen around us the bomb never stop and there is no transport left in the citi it s realli hard to work on rush of footag of bodi part and blood in the begin it s imposs to finish but you know you have to continu so you can show the world what s happen after a while these imag becom normal i am not afraid of the bomb hunger or injuri but when my littl brother ask me for food or sweet or when my mother tell me she is afraid or you feel afraid for your famili be injur then i feel scare and as though life ha no mean when you ar awai from home and you hear that there is a bomb or shoot close to your hous you can t just leav your job and go home you worri and your heart won t calm itself down until you know your famili is ok even though we got us to the bomb we ar innat afraid of hear the sound of a plane we alwai run to the closest thing to protect us from the bomb recent we can see the pilot insid the plane becaus thei fly so low you feel like the pilot is come to snatch live and leav the sound of a plane approach and the sound of machin gun fire ar the sound that take awai life
